However, Western countries view this economic growth positive for economic growth, job creation, and poverty reduction, but there are also millions who believe China is on the wrong path threatening jobs in the Western world, access to raw materials and new technology, which could plague the European and American society.

Security Council of the United Nations

At home for European powers, a variety of organizations which are open for every member of the European union to step in emerged in after the second World War. One of those was the Council of Europe, which focuses on the protection of rights and freedoms of all citizens of Europe. However, more than half of the Europeans citizens also supported a community that transcends national borders. The idea of the free movement of people, goods and information without restrictions has spread throughout the continent to make peace in Europe a viable possibility. Nevertheless, the expansion of the European Union brought about a variety of problems that EU-Commission started dealing with in the mid-20th century. Amongst the main challenges are the expanding economic gap between Western and former Eastern European states, the impact of the organizations policies on the global scale, and the EU in its internal relationship building. Many of these problems were handled in a way, that one could call crisis management.
